 \frac{1}{6} \binom{n-1}{r-1}  \left(\frac{5}{6}\right)^{n-r}  \left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^{r-1}.
p(z) = \sum_{n\ge r}  \binom{n-1}{r-1}  \left(\frac{5}{6}\right)^{n-r}  \left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^r z^n =  \left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^r  \left(\frac{6}{5}\right)^r \sum_{n\ge r}  \binom{n-1}{r-1}  \left(\frac{5}{6}\right)^n  z^n \\= \left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^r  \sum_{n\ge r}  \binom{n-1}{r-1}  \left(\frac{5}{6}\right)^n  z^n = \left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^r  \sum_{n\ge 0}  \binom{n+r-1}{r-1}  \left(\frac{5z}{6}\right)^{n+r} \\=  \left(\frac{z}{6}\right)^r  \sum_{n\ge 0}  \binom{n+r-1}{r-1}  \left(\frac{5z}{6}\right)^n.
 \sum_{n\ge 0}  \binom{n+r-1}{r-1} q^n = \frac{1}{(1-q)^r}
 p(z) = \left(\frac{z}{6}\right)^r  \frac{1}{(1-5z/6)^r} = \left(\frac{z}{6-5z} \right)^r
 [z^{20}]  \left(\frac{z}{6}\right)^5  \frac{1}{(1-5z/6)^5} = \left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^5 [z^{15}] \frac{1}{(1-5z/6)^5} = \left(\frac{1}{6}\right)^5 \binom{15+4}{4} \left( \frac{5}{6}\right)^{15} \sim 0.0323525. 
